<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\vx1_12_lantry\vx1_12_cv_berrytrip_chiasmus</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>77</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>"By now, I ought to have learned to grab a bucket before doing things like this."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Always a pleasure, brother Lantry."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>The vision of Nerat fades into a swirl of flames. Your surroundings ripple, distorted by the heat of a blinding summer day that seems barely tepid to your touch. A new figure emerges from the fire.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>The vision of Nerat explodes into a thick red fog that dissipates into a translucent crimson haze. Another figure steps out of the haze.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>The image of Nerat freezes in time, even the ever-moving flames of his outlines become rigid thorns of green. The Archon's body crumbles away, revealing a smaller figure underneath.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then what of my plan for a second Archive? Pretend I'm wrong, pretend [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] isn't coming. A second vault would be rings well spent considering the Schools of Tides and Wild-"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And it will be the third time I turn you down. Even the youngest scribe learns that repeating a thing does not make it more true."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Our defenses rival that of even Sentinel Stand Keep, yet you would waste our efforts building for the day they fail? My dear Lantry, stick to your Chronicles. Your job is to record our decisions, not to decide what the record will be."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Remain calm.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Address Lantry.] "An old friend of yours?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Address the [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url].] "Who are you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What happened to [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url]?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You know I hate it when you talk like that! Even the most addled scribe learns that covering your ears and doubting a fact doesn't make it go away. If we surrender before war breaks out, we have a chance to-"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The enemy needn't muster a single battalion and you're ready to give up? The very dumbest thing we can do is let the Overlord's reputation undo us without a fight. So long as I am in charge, we will not cower."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Remain calm.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your orders went from simple spying to swaying opinions?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So am I seeing your memories? These are some unusual berries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then you lead us into ruin! [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Redundant [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] was right, the last ten years have made us fat, foolish - addicted to prosperity! "</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You think me incautious? You think you're the only [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] telling me what MUST be done?! You impertinent little fuck, I know you have others swallowing the lies you ink them! Your absent-minded charade doesn't work on me. You poison their minds against me and have the gall to pretend like you're some well-meaninged mentor trying to be the kindly champion of the concerned student."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Now you're just doing it to enrage me! I think I will be alive to record you as the very final Provost of the School of Ink and Quill. May [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] prove me wrong, but this proud School will perish on your tenure."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Remain calm.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You've spoken about recording, not defining the record. You sound rather political here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So am I seeing your memories? These are some unusual berries."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then we are lucky that several dozen Sages are in line to inherit the Scrivener's Eye before it falls to you. But you worry too much, my dear Lantry - the way you see the world, we win either way."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] invades, well then we owe you one big 'you were right' and won't that make you feel great? And if [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] doesn't invade... well then you and everyone in the Tiers wins!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Chronicle will note your hubris."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Remain calm.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Not if an objective Chronicler is doing the writing. Your passion and convictions are a troublesome sign for one trusted to observe all things as they are. Perhaps you are not fit for this role."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"In fairness, you were right all along. Is that any consolation?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So how did you describe the School's passing in your Chronicle?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I uh, apologize for even mentioning this matter. I will take my leave."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Uh, yes - uh, [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Chiasmus. Provost of the School back before the war. Vapid bloviator, insufferable pedant - needless to say our similarities made us utterly incompatible."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"[url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] Chiasmus, Provost of the School of Ink and Quill. Did you have an audience scheduled? And how did you get in here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Voices? So that's what you were seeing. My condolences - after a drink from the memory well of dead scribes, the berries rewarded me. Even when I closed my eyes - breasts!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Not exactly. I think I started speaking well of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] here or there. Somehow, the Voices learned of it and encouraged me to keep it up."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see now why Lexeme's notes mention these berries will probably cause permanent insanity."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I was joyously studying history and so... on the one hand, I'm becoming fond of... certain peers and on the other hand, I'm learning that [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] is this inevitable, ever-consuming force."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So no, I didn't need to be ordered to advocate for [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]. It was merely the most expedient way to preserve the people I loved."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I uh... suppose this is not my finest moment of sporting an all-receptive mind. But we're talking about the fall of this whole realm - it seemed worth bending the rules to save it all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Remain calm.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see now why Lexeme's notes mention these berries will probably cause permanent insanity."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Did others see your point of view?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A handful, yes, but... my convictions placed me in an unpopular minority. Before the war, many thought fearing [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] akin to childish night terrors... most took me for a fool."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I think I... may have touched upon a certain provost being exceptionally daft but, for the sake of history, I did emphasize that ALL of the Sages were responsible for the School's collapse."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If one could purchase food and whores with smugness... maybe."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Breathe rapidly.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>Quickening your breath sends your heart racing. Whatever reaction the berries are having seems to settle in deeper.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>You once again muster your vigor, quickening your heart and lungs. In an instant, you feel gravity reach out with a wrathful hand. The world grows dark and silent.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>The emptiness fades and you rediscover a shred of your senses. Acting on their own, your limbs dart about, clumsily righting your posture.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you think I am BLIND to the Overlord? Because I do not act with your reactionary zeal does not mean I fail to act at all. We are of course taking precautions. A failure to plan, is a plan to fail, after all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>The outside world becomes dimmer, the chattering figures pantomime the acts of conversation but their words stretch into overlapping blurs that cascade into moments of roar and stretches of harmony.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Relax while you still can.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Breathe faster!]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your heart matches pace with your lungs, and soon the hammering in your chest drowns out the chatter, until the voices seem to flood into the spaces between heartbeats.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>84</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Insult of insults. Here he stands, warning of us of [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]... not telling us of the spy Nerat has already placed in our midst. He had the ability to warn us in a way we'd believe... but to do so would have meant risking his own hide... can't have that."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your vision swirls with blues and reds as scents of cinnamon and charred parchment assault your noise. Lantry's voice, as well as the voice of his [url=glossary:sage]Sage[/url] friend, warble through your ears as inchoate sounds, not discernible words.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>As your heart slows, you begin to recognize Lantry from the blur.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Become one with the silence.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Steady your breathing until your heartbeat is under your control.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>With several deep breaths, you begin to relax. The calming warmth of the berries sets deeper into your spine, dulling the sights and sounds around you while bringing to the fore of your mind every twitch, itch, and sensation running through your body.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>Your fingers burn as if set aflame, but your hands register only warmth and the rippling sensation of flowing air - pain is absent from the equation. With each beat of your heart, the fires at your fingertips flare and pulse.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Join with the flame.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>With a calm breath, you pull the flame inward, letting the heat conduct through bone and sinew until your whole body alights with fire. The [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Fire is always a part of you, whether you wish it or not.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Helplessly succumb to your doom.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>The flames burn hotter, sizzling your fingers until the smell of your own searing flesh drowns out your nostrils.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I uh, apologize for even mentioning this matter. I will take my leave."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>The sound of Lantry's voice snaps you out of your hallucination. Though still unable to control your body, the visions of your death fade into the blur of dreams.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>As the outside stimuli fade from your mind, you become aware of an electric jolt running through your body, the sensation peaking with each beat of your heart. Fog drips from your lips as your slightest exhalation leaves your body with gale force winds.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Join with the storm.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>Lightning arcs between your fingertips as you bring your hands together, closing the arcane circuit. The hairs on your body stand on end as the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Storms swells within you. Everywhere you travel, you take some small fragment of the tempest with you.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>100</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Helplessly succumb to your doom.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>101</ID>
      <DefaultText>You try to breathe but suck in only rain and snow, and the sensation of drowning in the cold starts your body shaking.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>102</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you relax into a state of calm, your heart slows until it seems to altogether stop. You let out one final gasp before growing perfectly still and heavy as your blood turns to stone, veins of quartz and feldspar displacing veins of blood.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Allow the transformation to happen.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>104</ID>
      <DefaultText>One last breath and your body slows to a crawl, becoming instantly leaden with solid mass. As soon as the calmness begins to bore, you give a small wiggle of your hand, and at once, your body returns to its fluid state.

Though it shows itself in the strangest of moments, the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Stone is still with you, and likely always will be.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>105</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Helplessly succumb to your doom.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>106</ID>
      <DefaultText>Unable to fight the slow petrification of your flesh, you try to look down at your own feet only to discover your eyes have frozen into gemstones and are now rooted into your granite skull.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
